Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
placePad(25.10)                                                placePad(25.10)

Name
       placePad - Places an I/O pad instance

Syntax
       placePad

       [-help]

       <pad_name>

       [<orientation>]

       <location >

       Places  an  I/O  pad  instance.  This  command  can  be used before the
       place_design command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each placePad parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man placePad.

       <location>
              Coordinates of new origin. The option is a point and a must.

       <orientation>
              Specifies  the  orientation  of the pad cell. Specify one of the
              following values: R0, R90, R180, R270, MX, MX90, MY, and MY90.

              Default: R0

       <pad_name>
              Specifies the pad instance name.

Example
       The following command places the I/O pad instance  with  mirrored  axis
       orientation, rotated 90 degrees counterclockwise:

       placePad SH14/I412 498.3 5000.8 MX90

Related Information
              * place_design

